The paper proposes a novel recurrent neural network architecture that improves accuracy and stability. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are all potential sub-categories that this paper could belong to. However, given the focus on neural networks and deep learning, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of autapse, which is a concept from neuroscience, which further supports the likelihood of cs.NE being a relevant sub-category.
